<subSubSection id="C317654C7003C36F4B88FE70FD2EFDFB" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB236C77003C36F4B88FE70FEFEFD9A" blockId="3.[174,1233,458,1829]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
Etymology. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4AE4FE71FE25FE5B" box="[399,464,459,484]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Terra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4AE4FE71FE25FE5B" box="[399,464,459,484]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Terra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Latin word for “ground, Earth”) and 
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F48DDFE71FC0EFE5B" box="[950,1019,459,484]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">nectes</emphasis>
(Greek word for “swimmer”), implying a semi-aquatic animal adapted more for terrestrial movement than aquatic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236C77003C36F4B88FD90FD2EFDFB" blockId="3.[174,1233,458,1829]" box="[227,731,554,581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
T y p e s p e c i e s. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4ACFFD91FD79FDFB" authority="Rahmat &amp; Koretsky &amp; Osborne &amp; Alford, 2017" authorityName="Rahmat &amp; Koretsky &amp; Osborne &amp; Alford" authorityYear="2017" box="[420,652,555,580]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Terranectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4ACFFD91FD79FDFB" box="[420,652,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Terranectes magnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F49F2FD90FD2EFDFB" bold="true" box="[665,731,554,580]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24A57AE7003C36F49F2FD90FD2EFDFB" box="[665,731,554,580]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C317654C7003C36F4B88FDF0FCA0FD3B" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BB236C77003C36F4B88FDF0FCA0FD3B" blockId="3.[174,1233,458,1829]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
Included species. In the Upper Miocene of the Chesapeake Group two new monachine species are recorded: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4958FDD1FD58FD3B" authorityName="Rahmat &amp; Koretsky &amp; Osborne &amp; Alford" authorityYear="2017" box="[563,685,619,644]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Terranectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnus">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4958FDD1FD58FD3B" box="[563,685,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">T. magnus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F498BFDD1FCA0FD3B" box="[736,853,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F498BFDD1FCA7FD3B" authorityName="Rahmat &amp; Koretsky &amp; Osborne &amp; Alford" authorityYear="2017" box="[736,850,619,644]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Terranectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="parvus">T. parvus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C317654C7003C3684B88FD30FC49FEF5" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB236C77003C36F4B88FD30FC0CFC9A" blockId="3.[174,1233,458,1829]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Diagnosis. Monachine seals of medium to large size. Posterior border of glenoid fossa of skull forms deep, wide postglenoid groove in tympanic bone; postglenoid foramen located at end of postglenoid groove, not floored by tympanic bone; long axis of tympanic bulla parallel to midline of skull; carotid canal parallel to surface of basioccipital, its posterior aperture opens ventrally, medial side has fully formed margin.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236C77003C36F4B88FC90FC53FB1A" blockId="3.[174,1233,458,1829]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
Humeral deltoid crest strongly developed, short, terminates at middle of diaphysis (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4A55FCF0FDD0FCDB" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[318,549,842,868]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Piscophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4A55FCF0FDD0FCDB" box="[318,549,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Piscophoca pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and in contrast to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F484CFCF0FBC7FCDB" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[807,1074,842,868]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F484CFCF0FBC7FCDB" box="[807,1074,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acrophoca longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4F2CFCF0FED4FC3B" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4F2CFCF0FED4FC3B" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pontophoca sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4A45FCD0FDE5FC3B" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[302,528,874,900]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4A45FCD0FDE5FC3B" box="[302,528,874,900]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4976FCD0FD1DFC3B" authorityName="Tavani" authorityYear="1941" box="[541,744,874,900]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pliophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4976FCD0FD1DFC3B" box="[541,744,874,900]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pliophoca etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); greater width of deltoid crest located on its proximal part (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4A9CFC30FD0FFC1B" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[503,762,906,932]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4A9CFC30FD0FFC1B" box="[503,762,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pontophoca sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F486DFC30FC27FC1B" authorityName="Tavani" authorityYear="1941" box="[774,978,906,932]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pliophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F486DFC30FC27FC1B" box="[774,978,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pliophoca etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and opposite to both 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4BC5FC11FECFFC7B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[174,314,938,964]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Piscophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4BC5FC11FECFFC7B" box="[174,314,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pis. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4A12FC10FDC1FC7B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[377,564,938,964]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4A12FC10FDC1FC7B" box="[377,564,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where entire deltoid crest approximately same width); in lateral view deltoid crest flattened and oval (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F480AFC71FC19FC5B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[865,1004,970,996]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Piscophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F480AFC71FC19FC5B" box="[865,1004,970,996]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pis. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4897FC70FB3FFC5B" authorityName="Tavani" authorityYear="1941" box="[1020,1226,970,996]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pliophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4897FC70FB3FFC5B" box="[1020,1226,970,996]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pliophoca etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and opposite from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4AE6FC50FDB0FBBB" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[397,581,1002,1028]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4AE6FC50FDB0FBBB" box="[397,581,1002,1028]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where deltoid crest significantly elongated; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4BC5FBB0FE65FB9B" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[174,400,1034,1060]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4BC5FBB0FE65FB9B" box="[174,400,1034,1060]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with flattened and square-shape); proximal end of deltoid crest higher than head (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4AC7FB90FD8DFBFB" authorityName="Tavani" authorityYear="1941" box="[428,632,1066,1092]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pliophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4AC7FB90FD8DFBFB" box="[428,632,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pliophoca etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; opposite to both 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4826FB91FC23FBFB" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[845,982,1066,1092]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Piscophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4826FB91FC23FBFB" box="[845,982,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pis. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4F7AFB90FB3CFBFB" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[1041,1225,1066,1092]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4F7AFB90FB3CFBFB" box="[1041,1225,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where they have same height; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F49D9FBF0FC4DFBDB" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[690,952,1098,1124]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F49D9FBF0FC4DFBDB" box="[690,952,1098,1124]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pontophoca sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with lesser trochanter higher than head and deltoid crest; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F486BFBD0FC1DFB3B" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[768,1000,1130,1156]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F486BFBD0FC1DFB3B" box="[768,1000,1130,1156]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with deltoid crest located below lesser tubercle and below or at same level as head).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236C77003C36F4B88FB10FB82F93A" blockId="3.[174,1233,458,1829]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
Femoral greater trochanter extends proximally slightly higher than head (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4BC5FB70FE47FB5B" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[174,434,1226,1252]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4BC5FB70FE47FB5B" box="[174,434,1226,1252]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pontophoca sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F49EAFB70FCCFFB5B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[641,826,1226,1252]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F49EAFB70FCCFFB5B" box="[641,826,1226,1252]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where greater trochanter extends much higher; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4A87FB50FD26FABB" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[492,723,1258,1284]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4A87FB50FD26FABB" box="[492,723,1258,1284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with head extending higher than greater trochanter; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4AA3FAB0FD63FA9B" authorityName="Tavani" authorityYear="1941" box="[456,662,1290,1316]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pliophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4AA3FAB0FD63FA9B" box="[456,662,1290,1316]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pliophoca etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with head at same level as greater trochanter); greater trochanter proximal part wider than distal (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F48EAFA90FBCCFAFB" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[897,1081,1322,1348]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F48EAFA90FBCCFAFB" box="[897,1081,1322,1348]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4F2CFA90FED4FADB" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4F2CFA90FED4FADB" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pontophoca sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4A44FAF0FDE6FADB" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[303,531,1354,1380]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4A44FAF0FDE6FADB" box="[303,531,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); trochanteric fossa deep, wide, and open distally, reaching the distal border of head (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4917FAD0FC91FA3B" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[636,868,1386,1412]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4917FAD0FC91FA3B" box="[636,868,1386,1412]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4F67FAD0FB3CFA3B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[1036,1225,1386,1412]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4F67FAD0FB3CFA3B" box="[1036,1225,1386,1412]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4BC5FA30FE47FA1B" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[174,434,1418,1444]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4BC5FA30FE47FA1B" box="[174,434,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pontophoca sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4A84FA30FD48FA1B" authorityName="Tavani" authorityYear="1941" box="[495,701,1418,1444]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pliophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4A84FA30FD48FA1B" box="[495,701,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pliophoca etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); intertrochanteric line disappears at middle of diaphysis (opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4A8BFA10FD6FFA7B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[480,666,1450,1476]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4A8BFA10FD6FFA7B" box="[480,666,1450,1476]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with longer intertrochanteric line; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4BC5FA70FE61FA5B" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[174,404,1482,1508]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4BC5FA70FE61FA5B" box="[174,404,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with very short intertrochanteric line; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4F69FA70FB24FA5B" authorityName="Tavani" authorityYear="1941" box="[1026,1233,1482,1508]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pliophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4F69FA70FB24FA5B" box="[1026,1233,1482,1508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pliophoca etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4B88FA50FE12F9BB" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[227,487,1514,1540]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4B88FA50FE12F9BB" box="[227,487,1514,1540]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pontophoca sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with undeveloped line); supracondylar fossa shallow, slender, elongated, and located above lateral condyle (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4846F9B0FBFBF99B" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[813,1038,1546,1572]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4846F9B0FBFBF99B" box="[813,1038,1546,1572]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4FCBF9B0FEDAF9FB" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4FCBF9B0FEDAF9FB" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with deeper and larger supracondylar fossa; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F48A6F990FB25F9FB" baseAuthorityName="Alekseev" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[973,1232,1578,1604]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pontophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sarmatica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F48A6F990FB25F9FB" box="[973,1232,1578,1604]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pontophoca sarmatica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4B8CF9F0FE4DF9DB" authorityName="Tavani" authorityYear="1941" box="[231,440,1610,1636]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pliophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4B8CF9F0FE4DF9DB" box="[231,440,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pliophoca etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with more horizontally-directed supracondylar fossa); condyles unequal in size (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4A8EF9D0FD68F93B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[485,669,1642,1668]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4A8EF9D0FD68F93B" box="[485,669,1642,1668]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F49C0F9D0FC78F93B" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[683,909,1642,1668]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F49C0F9D0FC78F93B" box="[683,909,1642,1668]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F48F0F9D0FB93F93B" authorityName="Tavani" authorityYear="1941" box="[923,1126,1642,1668]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Pliophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="etrusca">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F48F0F9D0FB93F93B" box="[923,1126,1642,1668]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pliophoca etrusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB236C77003C3684B88F930FE2CFE95" blockId="3.[174,1233,458,1829]" lastBlockId="4.[166,1225,175,330]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
Innominate bone similar to typical monachines, without lateral excavation (same as 
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4BC5F911FE03F97B" box="[174,502,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4BC5F911FECDF97B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[174,312,1706,1732]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Piscophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacifica">Pis. pacifica</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4A2BF910FE03F97B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[320,502,1706,1732]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">Acr. longirostris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4969F910FD17F97B" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[514,738,1706,1732]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4969F910FD17F97B" box="[514,738,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); wide, flattened iliac crest (opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4FCCF911FEF2F95B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Piscophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4FCCF911FEF2F95B" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pis. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with rounded and short iliac crest and opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4802F970FBD7F95B" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[873,1058,1738,1764]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4802F970FBD7F95B" box="[873,1058,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with rounded iliac crest that is less wider than 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4952F951FD4AF8BB" authorityName="Rahmat &amp; Koretsky &amp; Osborne &amp; Alford" authorityYear="2017" box="[569,703,1771,1796]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Terranectes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4952F951FD4AF8BB" box="[569,703,1771,1796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Terranectes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and more wider than 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F48BBF951FBA9F8BB" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[976,1116,1770,1796]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Piscophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F48BBF951FBA9F8BB" box="[976,1116,1770,1796]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Pis. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447003C36F4BA4F8B0FE41F89B" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[207,436,1802,1828]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57003C36F4BA4F8B0FE41F89B" box="[207,436,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Callophoca obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with rounded, thick and wide iliac crest); thick specifically across acetabulum (similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447004C3684ADCFF0AFDB5FF76" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[439,576,175,201]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Piscophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57004C3684ADCFF0AFDB5FF76" box="[439,576,175,201]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">Pis. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447004C368486FFF0AFC49FF76" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[772,956,175,202]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57004C368486FFF0AFC49FF76" box="[772,956,175,202]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); reduced iliopectineal eminence (opposite to both 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447004C3684A94FF6AFD79FF56" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[511,652,207,233]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Piscophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57004C3684A94FF6AFD79FF56" box="[511,652,207,233]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">Pis. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447004C36849A5FF6AFC7CFF56" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[718,905,207,234]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Acrophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="longirostris">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57004C36849A5FF6AFC7CFF56" box="[718,905,207,234]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">Acr. longirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and shallow acetabulum (similar to 
<emphasis id="B979EAD57004C3684A44FF55FDE9FEB6" box="[303,540,239,265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447004C3684A44FF55FDE0FEB6" baseAuthorityName="Van Beneden" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[303,533,239,265]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Callophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">Callophoca obscura</taxonomicName>
;
</emphasis>
opposite to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D4D447004C36849D3FF4AFCB1FEB6" authorityName="de Muizon" authorityYear="1981" box="[696,836,239,265]" class="Mammalia" family="Phocidae" genus="Piscophoca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="4" pageNumber="225" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pacifica">
<emphasis id="B979EAD57004C36849D3FF4AFCB1FEB6" box="[696,836,239,265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="225">Pis. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
